duck: Construction set - A construction set is a set of standardized pieces that allow for the construction of a variety of different models.
Chess set - Chess pieces, or chessmen, are the pieces deployed on a chessboard to play the game of chess.
Radio set - An antique radio is a radio receiving set that is collectible because of its age and rarity.
set definition: to cause to sit.
Set (darts), when one player wins three legs
Set (mathematics), A collection of well defined and distinct objects
Chemistry set - A chemistry set is an educational toy allowing the user (typically a teenager) to perform simple chemistry experiments.
Tea set - A tea set, in the Western tradition, is a set of dishes sold in a group for use at afternoon tea or a formal tea party.
Television set - A television set is a device that combines a tuner, display, and speakers for the purpose of viewing television.
Set theory - Set theory is the branch of mathematics that studies sets, which are collections of objects.
Set (mythology) or Seth, an ancient Egyptian deity
